main event: A civilian reported seeing one red light and one white light in the sky over Indianapolis, Indiana, on May 7, 1966.
interesting points: The sighting involved two lights, one red and one white, observed at night,The object was noted to be duller than the moon or street lights,Description indicated the object drifted with no sound and was the color orange,The observer reported a length of observation of about 20 seconds,The report concludes that there was insufficient data for evaluation.
sighted object: one red light and one white light
